{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Remediated review findings f17ce70ba6939effc, f13b739f1cc02edc6, and fe9fdb8d2cc5f8c06. The focused verifier now has one canonical split algorithm (whole records, then a singleton findings tuple, never plan text); batch-step with: delivery is explicitly implemented through backward-compatible BatchRunRequest.with_inputs and interpreter resolution with named tests/files; and DET blockers now dominate prerequisite indeterminacy, yielding unsigned BLOCK with the coverage flag while no-DET indeterminacy yields unsigned INDETERMINATE. This precedence preserves known deterministic failures instead of masking them."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784572944952955001,"uuid":"4f462d36-04b5-4223-8c5b-7178c57895dc"}